\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs20 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Then came the next frontier: beat timing.\
Beat detection is a notoriously gnarly problem, but one that\'92s already been tackled by countless DJ tools. After some deep dives and trial runs with open-source libraries, Aubio emerged as a strong contender. Still, it didn\'92t quite nail my use case\'97it lacked a constant beat assumption, which is actually true for 99.9999% of the tracks I listen to.\
The eureka moment came from poking around in the Mixxx source code (bless open-source). There, I found an elegant implementation built around the Queen Mary (not Queens College!) beat detection algorithm, beautifully optimized for consistency. I adapted and extended that idea, adding bar detection for an extra layer of timing intelligence.\
This rhythm-awareness unlocked a wave of beat-synced animations\'97like the \'93dancing cover art\'94 on the song detection panel, a quirky but surprisingly delightful feature. At the moment, my biggest limit is my lacking creativity. I finally have all the tools at hand to do really funky stuff, yet no really new ideas manifest. I\'92ve recently discovered Synesthesia - amazing tool - I may at some point start borrowing some of their shaders. \
