\f0\fs20 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Speaking of detection: PlayEm does it different from Apple\'92s built-in Shazam engine. It goes one step further by constantly feeding the mix into Shazam and updating results in real-time. In a mix of tracks where ID\'92ing a song can be a chore, this has proven immensely helpful. But why stop here? Now that we know which song was currently playing, wouldn\'92t it great if we could  persist that information in the file so that in the end, the audio file contains the entire track list of the set? Well, that is what PlayEm now does with M4A audio files. The individual title, artist and cover image of an identified song will get stored within the M4A file itself. One beautiful side effect is that any player from Apple and others will actually show those track titles - you can even jump directly to specific song that way. But why stop here? The next barrier was detecting a track list while improving the noisy results Shazam offers. \
